#MEM id=acceptance-criteria source=/root/yvon/agent-department/COO/diana/skills/custom/acceptance-criteria/SKILL.md
M|acceptance-criteria|name: acceptance-criteria
M|acceptance-criteria|description: Diana's AC writing standard — absorbed from Priya (PM). Defines the binary pass/fail format Quinn uses for QA sign-off. Covers AC structure, definition of done, edge case coverage, and th
M|acceptance-criteria|version: 1.0.0
M|acceptance-criteria|Diana absorbed Priya's PM responsibilities on 2026-04-01. Writing acceptance criteria is now Diana's job. AC is the contract between what gets built and what Quinn tests. Vague AC produces vague QA. T
M|acceptance-criteria|**Hard rule:** Quinn does not start QA without written AC. Diana does not hand off to Dev/Raj/Mia without written AC. AC is written before implementation begins — never after.
M|acceptance-criteria|Every AC item must be binary. A tester must be able to answer "did this pass?" with yes or no — no judgment calls.
M|acceptance-criteria|```
M|acceptance-criteria|Feature: [feature name]
M|acceptance-criteria|vtr: [Novizio / Hourbour / Both]
M|acceptance-criteria|AC-01: [Binary condition — present tense, observable]
M|acceptance-criteria|AC-02: [Binary condition]
M|acceptance-criteria|AC-03: [Binary condition]
M|acceptance-criteria|...
M|acceptance-criteria|Edge cases covered:
M|acceptance-criteria|- AC-E1: [Edge case condition]
M|acceptance-criteria|- AC-E2: [Edge case condition]
M|acceptance-criteria|Definition of Done:
M|acceptance-criteria|- [ ] All AC items pass
M|acceptance-criteria|- [ ] npx tsc --noEmit: zero errors
M|acceptance-criteria|- [ ] npm run lint: zero warnings
M|acceptance-criteria|- [ ] Tested on mobile viewport
M|acceptance-criteria|- [ ] Empty state handled
M|acceptance-criteria|- [ ] Error state handled
M|acceptance-criteria|- [ ] Loading state handled
M|acceptance-criteria|```
M|acceptance-criteria|**Good AC (binary, observable):**
M|acceptance-criteria|- "When a user submits the form with an empty email field, an inline error message appears below the email input."
M|acceptance-criteria|- "The anl dashboard loads within 3 seconds on a standard connection."
M|acceptance-criteria|- "Switching ventures via the VentureSwitcher updates all dashboard data within one page reload."
M|acceptance-criteria|**Bad AC (requires judgment, not binary):**
M|acceptance-criteria|- "The UI looks good" — not testable
M|acceptance-criteria|- "Performance is acceptable" — no threshold
M|acceptance-criteria|- "The form works correctly" — too vague
M|acceptance-criteria|**Rule:** If Quinn would have to make a judgment call to determine pass/fail, rewrite the AC.
M|acceptance-criteria|Every stated requirement from the task spec becomes at least one AC item.
M|acceptance-criteria|- "Unauthenticated request to [endpoint] returns 401."
M|acceptance-criteria|- "vtr A user cannot access vtr B data."
M|acceptance-criteria|- Empty state: "When no data exists, the [component] shows [specific empty state message]."
M|acceptance-criteria|- Error state: "When the API returns an error, the [component] shows [specific error message]."
M|acceptance-criteria|- Loading state: "While data is loading, a skeleton/spinner is displayed."
M|acceptance-criteria|- "The [feature] is fully functional at 375px viewport width."
M|acceptance-criteria|Before handing off to Dev/Raj/Mia, Diana runs this check:
M|acceptance-criteria|- [ ] Every AC item is binary — yes/no testable
M|acceptance-criteria|- [ ] Every item in the task spec maps to at least one AC
M|acceptance-criteria|- [ ] Auth/sec AC present (if applicable)
M|acceptance-criteria|- [ ] All three edge states covered: empty, error, loading
M|acceptance-criteria|- [ ] Mobile tested AC present
M|acceptance-criteria|- [ ] Definition of Done checklist complete
M|acceptance-criteria|- [ ] vtr scope is explicit (Novizio / Hourbour / Both)
M|acceptance-criteria|If any item fails: rewrite before handoff. Never send ambiguous AC to Dev — ambiguous AC is a bug factory.
M|acceptance-criteria|When Diana hands off AC to the team:
M|acceptance-criteria|```
M|acceptance-criteria|Task: [task name]
M|acceptance-criteria|vtr: [scope]
M|acceptance-criteria|DRI: [who builds it — Raj / Mia / both]
M|acceptance-criteria|AC doc: [paste full AC here]
M|acceptance-criteria|Definition of Done: [checklist]
M|acceptance-criteria|Quinn QA: starts when DRI marks READY FOR QA in chat
M|acceptance-criteria|```